data.title: Dusk "Dusk" self-titled 1994
data.meta_description:
Dusk "Dusk" self-titled 1994 by Dusk, released 01 January 1994

1. Envision The Terror
2. Element Of Symmetry
3. Begotten Interlude
4. Dreamscape
5. Consigned To Oblivion
6. Mourning Shadow

"Dusk" Original self-titled 1994 EP
data.text:
1.

Envision The Terror 03:59

ENVISION THE TERROR Follow me, into obscurity I'll lead you...to a domain of dreaded existence One where the tortured spirits deplore Cries from beyond are heard At one with fire, our lord Welcome to the Afterlife Too late to cry for compassion now Haven chosen non-repentance Blistering winds consume your flesh Ghouls all to see, unholy beaconing Searing tides, deplete your soul

2.

Element Of Symmetry 04:32

ELEMENT OF SYMMETRY Woeful times now awakening, black rain fall Hated minds from the other side, engaged in writhe Shadows of the deep have spoken Fortune unclear Entity entrancing Substance energy The elemental plane of balance dismantled Benign fantasies are present Lament the loss of comprehension Darkened body lies frail Look beyond the veil

3.

Begotten Interlude 04:09

BEGOTTEN INTERLUDE The grace of our lands elaborate regression Our sacred momento, a failed trial An indication of feeble intellect Seize the day Pitiful dismay Impending decay A vision...He's come The petals of ecstasy, intense delight dismissed This foresight is now real Anticipate with great fear the second advent Seize the day Truth divine He's come Biblical prophecy, embalmed reality

4.

Dreamscape 03:13

DREAMSCAPE Buried inside my brain lies many complications I am exploring a world of illusion Mind deteriorates Inscription of malfeasance inbetted throughout Growing apparition commands Casting depravement upon creation Obliteration rendered The phantom again returns through the image I commence fortification Vivid hallucinations sojourn Subconsciously plagued. Epoch recedes Momentary lapse of reason. Quest for tranquility Subliminal mutation. Dwindle away. Vanish

5.

Consigned To Oblivion 05:43

CONSIGNED TO OBLIVION Bestowed hatred unveiled at last Leviathan unleashed from the ancient past Gaze into the light, it's glowing dim Renounce the dread reign in sin Detriment to society Your departure downcast to me Comatose state final abode Dystopia exposed, destiny unfolds Requiems of disgust prevail Entrance to the world of betrayal Modern youth, self destructive Hurtling toward a senseless dungeon Come feel the pain Consigned to oblivion, eradication of man Chaotic prevalence, affliction, tolerance Subjective mind, life destroyed Feeling contempt not resolved Witchery, mass deception Live to forget humanity Emptiness deep inside Nightmare, torment at last Isolated world, shriveled past...

6.

Mourning Shadow 05:04
